Robbie Williams is an English singer-songwriter and entertainer who rose to fame as a member of the boy band Take That. He was born on February 13, 1974, in Stoke-on-Trent, Staffordshire, England. After leaving Take That in 1995, Williams embarked on a successful solo career, selling over 75 million records worldwide.
